  "text": "When participants were asked to step over two obstacles located 1 m apart, their foot placement to take off prior to the first obstacle was closer to the obstacle than when they were stepping over a single obstacle [CITATION_1] . This is also an understandable method in order to obtain a better take-off position prior to a second obstacle and suggests that the modification of limb movement for avoiding the second obstacle was already initiated before stepping over the first one.",
